- "Bloom above the average GDP" refers to regions with a GDP higher than the average GDP across all regions;
- "Vast garden of economic growth" is a metaphor for the economic landscape across different regions and countries.

sql:
SELECT region_id, AVG(petrol_consumption) AS avg_petrol_consumption
FROM petrol_consumption
GROUP BY region_id;

